commit.message:
Release 2.0.24

Signed-off-by: Daiki Ueno <ueno@gnu.org>
Add workaround for building gpgme with musl >= 1.2.4
Remove duplicated tests

Add the `ignore_mdc_error` flag setter and getter

Add generic `get_ctx_flag` getter and `set_ctx_flag` setter

Don't add gem root to LOAD_PATH

The comment, "C extension is in the root", is no longer accurate. It's
in ext/ which will be added to the LOAD_PATH by bundler or rubygems.

Revert comment about cleaning not being on by default

Cleaning is on by default; it's just that prior to #168 the cleaning
was quietly failing:

```
Cleaning files only used during build.
/Users/stanhu/.asdf/installs/ruby/3.1.4/lib/ruby/3.1.0/fileutils.rb:637:in `rm_rf': wrong number of arguments (given 2, expected 1) (ArgumentError)
	from ./extconf.rb:28:in `block in <main>'
	from <internal:dir>:220:in `glob'
	from ./extconf.rb:27:in `glob'
	from ./extconf.rb:27:in `<main>'
make: [clean-ports] Error 1 (ignored)
```

Fix --clean option

Previously this was not working due to this error:

```
ruby/3.1.4/lib/ruby/3.1.0/fileutils.rb:637:in `rm_rf': wrong number of arguments (given 2, expected 1) (ArgumentError)
	from extconf.rb:33:in `<main>'
```

Also update the documentation to reflect that --clean is not enabled
by default.

Release 2.0.23

Signed-off-by: Daiki Ueno <ueno@gnu.org>

Update bundled libgpg-error and gpgme dependencies

Signed-off-by: Daiki Ueno <ueno@gnu.org>
Remove reserved value and update arity to 3

Fix: incompatible function pointer types with gpgme_op_keylist_ext_start
	- Fix issue #171
Add Ruby 3.2 to CI pipeline
Bump libassuan dependencies
fix: rubydoc URL

Improve checks for pkg-config and fall back to gpgme-config

https://github.com/ueno/ruby-gpgme/pull/166 changed from `pkg-config`
to `gpgme-config`, but if `PKG_CONFIG_PATH` is not set properly, the C
extension library will quietly build without the right linker
dependencies.

To fix this, we now check for the existence of `gpgme.pc` in
`PKG_CONFIG_PATH` and attempt to fall back to `gpgme-config` if it
does not exist.

Closes https://github.com/ueno/ruby-gpgme/issues/167
Release 2.0.22

Prefer pkg-config over gpgme-config

See https://bugs.debian.org/1023601 for context.

Undefine the alloc Ctx, Data and Key functions

See https://bugs.ruby-lang.org/issues/18007 and https://ruby-doc.org/core-3.1.1/doc/extension_rdoc.html#label-C+struct+to+Ruby+object
Make mini_portile2 less restrictive
Use coveralls_reborn
Update build status badge
Release 2.0.21
Bump libgpg-error, libassuan, and gpgme dependencies

As we replace pinentry-program in the gpg-agent.conf, the tests can't

bumped gpgme for bugfixes

Maybe this will show up as verified?

One more try at GPG verification
Update mini_portile dependency version to 2.7.0
Migrate CI to GitHub actions

Add .editorconfig file

To set the editor settings to a standard style.
Adding setting to:
- Use 2 space indentation
- Trim trailing white space

update-indentation-type-inconsistency

This PR should only contain white space changes.
I noticed some inconsistency in the use of tabs verses spaces for the indentation. Some editors display them slightly differently causing the indentation to appear oddly.

I replaced each tab with 8 spaces because that seemed to line up similar to the way github was displaying the code.

Feel free to ignore if this is incorrect or too petty of a request

Update crypto.rb

Typo on symmetric.
